Wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}. Dice @Roma tomato{1}. Zest @lime{1} until you have 1 tsp; quarter lime. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Slice @corn on the cob{1} kernels off cob; discard cob. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}; mince a few slices until you have 1 tsp. Mince @chili pepper{1}, removing ribs and seeds first for less heat.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over high heat (if using a nonstick pan, heat without oil). Add corn kernels and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and slightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}. (TIP: If corn begins to pop, cover pan with a #lid{}.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add sliced shallot and cook, stirring, until lightly browned and softened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Set aside 1 tsp garlic, then add remaining garlic to pan. Season with salt and pepper and stir to combine. Stir in cooked veggies, @tomato paste{3%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @cumin{1%tsp}, and ¼ cup water. Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

To #bowl{} with corn, add cilantro, minced shallot, reserved 1 tsp garlic, remaining cumin, juice from 2 lime wedges, and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper and stir to thoroughly combine.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, lime zest, salt, and pepper. Stir in water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}. Fill each tortilla with pork mixture, tomato, and chimichurri. Drizzle with crema. Garnish with chili if desired. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.